org.apache.lens.server.query.collect

Class ThreadSafeEstimatedQueryCollection

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.apache.lens.server.query.collect.ThreadSafeEstimatedQueryCollection
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EstimatedImmutableQueryCollection, ImmutableQueryCollection, EstimatedQueryCollection, MutableQueryCollection

    public class ThreadSafeEstimatedQueryCollection
extends Object
implements EstimatedQueryCollection
    Makes an implementation of EstimatedQueryCollection interface thread safe by wrapping all behaviours in synchronized method.

      • getQueries

        public Set<QueryContext> getQueries(LensDriver driver)
        Specified by:
        getQueries in interface EstimatedImmutableQueryCollection
        Parameters:
        driver - Driver for which queries have to be returned.
        Returns:
        A set of queries for which given driver is the selected driver. A new set is created and returned. Elements in the set are not cloned or copied. Multiple iterations over returned set are guaranteed to be in same order. If there are no queries, then an empty set is returned. null is never returned.

      • getQueries

        public Set<QueryContext> getQueries()
        Specified by:
        getQueries in interface ImmutableQueryCollection
        Returns:
        A new set copied from this collection of queries. Elements in the set are not cloned or copied. Multiple iterations over returned set are guaranteed to be in same order. If there are no queries, then an empty set is returned. null is never returned.

      • getQueries

        public Set<QueryContext> getQueries(String user)
        Specified by:
        getQueries in interface ImmutableQueryCollection
        Parameters:
        user - User for whom queries have to be returned.
        Returns:
        A set of queries submitted by the given user. A new set is created and returned. Elements in the set are not cloned or copied. Multiple iterations over returned set are guaranteed to be in same order. If there are no queries, then an empty set is returned. null is never returned.
